[SN]TITLE[SN]
World Indoor Bowls: Nick Brett and Robert Paxton reach final

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
English duo Nick Brett and Robert Paxton progressed to the World Indoor Bowls singles final as David Gourlay and holder Alex Marshall bowed out.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Brett claimed a 6-7 7-6 2-0 victory over Gourlay in the first semi-final.
And Paxton recovered from a heavy first set defeat to overcome Gourlay's fellow Scotsman and six-time champion Marshall 3-12 7-4 2-1.
The final takes place at the Potters Resort in Norfolk on Sunday at 14:00 GMT and will be live on BBC Two.
You can also watch it live on the BBC Sport website and app.
Neither world number one Brett nor Paxton have previously won the men's singles title but both have a pairs title to their name.
